      <hedline>
        <hl1>A 20th-Century Horror</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gregory S Kinojan letter says May 10 article on Turkey's massacre of Armenians shines light on 20th-century atrocity that history has largely ignored and Turkey has long denied</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your May 10 news article ''Turkish Region Recalls Massacre of Armenians'' shines light on a 20th-century atrocity that history has largely ignored.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your May 10 news article ''Turkish Region Recalls Massacre of Armenians'' shines light on a 20th-century atrocity that history has largely ignored.</p>
        <p>Written eyewitness accounts leave no doubt that a large-scale, systematic elimination of Armenians in Turkey was carried out. Nearly all of the actual survivors have long since died.</p>
        <p>Official denial of the massacres by Turkish governments, past and present, and overt efforts to conceal the truth perpetuate general enmity and distrust between the Turkish and Armenian peoples.</p>
        <p>GREGORY S. KINOIAN  Paramus, N.J., May 10, 2000</p>
      </block>
